Bottom line, Congress and the American people have more questions, we need to hear from Special Counsel Mueller before we draw any final conclusions. #MuellerReport
The findings in this report would be detrimental to any other President. As colorfully mentioned in the report, even Trump believed this would ‘end his presidency’.

Barr offered his own (press play) conclusion that the president did not obstruct justice while Mueller's report appears to undercut that finding. Mueller Report suggested Congress take action on at least TEN instances where the president sought to interfere in the probe
First, Barr spoke more like Trump’s political armor press secretary than an impartial Attorney General...
As a former prosecutor, I have always waited until I have all the facts before I come to any determination. We should let the full report speak for itself, and it must be made public.

It is unusual practice for an Attorney General to hold a press conference before releasing the full report to Congress or the American people. AG Barr should be impartial and not shape public perception before we have seen it the report.
